ol.li:
Here is an example NAD to create a Layer 2 kernel/veth
                    access-mode interface with static
                        IPAM:apiVersion: "k8s.cni.cncf.io/v1"
kind: NetworkAttachmentDefinition
metadata:
  name: vswitch-pod1-bd100
spec:
  config: '{
    "cniVersion":"0.4.0",
    "name": "vswitch-pod1-bd100",
    "plugins": [
      {
        "type": "jcnr",
        "args": {
          "instanceName": "vswitch",
          "instanceType": "virtual-switch",
	   "interfaceType": "veth",
          "bridgeDomain": "bd100",
          "bridgeVlanId": "100"
        },
        "ipam": {
          "type": "static",
          "addresses":[
            {
              "address":"99.61.0.2/16",
              "gateway":"99.61.0.1"
            },
            {
              "address":"1234::99.61.0.2/120",
              "gateway":"1234::99.61.0.1"
            }
          ]
        },
        "kubeConfig":"/etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf"
      }
    ]
  }'
The
                        NAD defines a bridge domain bd100 under which a
                            veth type pod interface should be attached in the
                            virtual-switch instance. It also defines a static
                    IP address to be assigned to the pod interface.
